parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause electrical shorts, leading to fires, stalling, and brake failure, which can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
Electrical system fires can spread quickly, causing damage to the vehicle and potentially leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
The failure of the driver's seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to malfunction, leading to a potential increase in the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt retractor fails to retract
the seat belt disconnects or unlocks
the seat belt will no longer latch
the red release button cracks and contaminates the latching mechanism.

symptoms: pieces of rubber flying off and damaging surrounding components.

no matter how hard the pedal is pressed
brakes return to normal after stopping with emergency brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of multiple electrical systems can cause a loss of critical vehicle functions, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
